## Open Science

European Commission, 2016:

> Open Science represents a new approach to the scientific process based on **cooperative work** and new ways of **diffusing knowledge** by using **digital technologies** and new **collaborative tools**.  

OECD, 2015:  

> "(...) to make the primary outputs of **publicly funded research results** – publications and the research data – **publicly accessible in digital format** with no or minimal restriction.  

## Are there some principles for going open?

Using FAIR principles ([go-fair.org](https://www.go-fair.org/fair-principles/)), i.e. improving:  
- **F**indability  
- **A**ccessibility  
- **I**nteroperability  
- **R**euse  

